Hi. My name is Stina and I am a rl female that variably plays male toons <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
My first ever char I created was in fact a male Wood Elf Rogue on the server that begins with the letter A. Dont remember the name of it. He still exists at level 1 or 2. On this char I discovered the gamma correction. After falling off Kelethin of course.<br>
<br>
I later recreated him on Drinal and he has been my main ever since. Even though he is only 25th level and dont get played much. This char I learned the newbie game. I even got my very first res on this char. I didnt even know what the box was that I clicked yes to. A very nice dwarven Cleric that was.<br>
<br>
Since him I have created various other toons (the annoying alt-itis syndrome), males and females. I have a woman cleric, woman enchanter and woman mage for instance. A man necro, man ranger, and a man sk are just few of my alts.<br>
<br>
Although I really love playing female toons, there are times when I just prefer to play male toons because then I can be like 'one of the boys'. I do feel a difference in peoples attitude towards me depending on what gender I am. And that is not just on the roleplaying server. Just on the normal bluebee servers.<br>
<br>
But it is not a bad attitude that I get. On the contrary. People are very nice on Drinal and respectful towards you if you are a woman. And I have never really experience discomfort from male chars towards my female chars. Even on the more exotic ones. They just respond to me as a woman differently then they respond to a man.<br>
<br>
But enough about me. The guy was a fool jumpin on you for being a man. I see nothing wrong with gender-switching in game and I can tell you it is quite very much common.<br>
<br>
Oh and the chars I listed below. Are both male and created on this server. On my third account I will probably make a lady.<br>
<br>
Stina1701.<br>
Tomkin, Karana Human Cleric.<br>
Istil, Rallos Sek Dark Elf/Wood Elf Warrior. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=celosilverhand>Celo Silverhand</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/31/03 12:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3921.topic&index=82>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: In the eyes of the FV Community...Id like to know</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Although I really love playing female toons, there are times when I just prefer to play male toons because then I can be like 'one of the boys'.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
